data.chText: 炭，木炭（可作燃料或供作画）
data.enText: a black substance made by burning wood slowly in an oven with little air. Charcoal is used as a fuel or for drawing.

tr: a stick of black carbon material used for drawing
a drawing made with a stick of black carbon material
a carbonaceous material obtained by heating wood or other organic matter in the absence of air
draw, trace, or represent with charcoal

value.def: Charcoal is a black substance obtained by burning wood without much air. It can be burned as a fuel, and small sticks of it are used for drawing with.
value.tran: 木炭;(用于绘画的)炭笔，木炭条
